'''Rock, Paper, Shotgun'''（翻譯名稱：'''岩石、紙張、獵槍'''）是一個網站專門為[[電腦遊戲|電腦遊戲]]和電腦遊戲業提供評價和分析。網站由Alec Meer、Jim Rossignol、Adam Smith、John Walkerv、Kieron Gillen、Quintin Smith<ref name="about">{{cite web|url = http://www.rockpapershotgun.com/about/|title = About Rock, Paper, Shotgun|publisher = Rock, Paper, Shotgun|author = Staff|accessdate = 2009-06-30|archive-url = https://www.webcitation.org/69VEXNieb?url=http://www.rockpapershotgun.com/about/|archive-date = 2012-07-28|dead-url = yes}}</ref>於2007年7月成立。在2010年，它與[[Eurogamer|Eurogamer]]合作成為了其中一位編者 。

岩石、紙張、獵槍是一個相當權威的遊戲新聞網站，往往許多是指它和使用它作為參考<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.heroesofstalingrad.com/2011/02/16/ro-is-very-important-says-rock-paper-shotgun/ |title=RO is “Very Important” Rock Paper Shotgun – and PC Gamer Top 100! |author=Alan Wilson |publisher=heroesofstalingrad.com |datepublished= |accessdate= |language=en |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69VEJrCPp?url=http://www.heroesofstalingrad.com/2011/02/16/ro-is-very-important-says-rock-paper-shotgun/ |archivedate=2012-07-28 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://planetbattlefield.gamespy.com/fullstory.php?id=164604 |title=Ben Cousins Interview with Rock, Paper, Shotgun |author=Scott |publisher=[[GameSpy|GameSpy]] |datepublished= |accessdate= |language=en |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69VEKMm7t?url=http://planetbattlefield.gamespy.com/fullstory.php?id=164604 |archivedate=2012-07-28 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://massively.joystiq.com/2008/09/07/rock-paper-shotgun-discovers-that-wow-is-a-dirty-word/ |title=Rock, Paper, Shotgun discovers that WoW is a "dirty word" |author=Samuel Axon |publisher=[[Joystiq|Joystiq]] |datepublished= |accessdate= |language=en |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69VELBizu?url=http://massively.joystiq.com/2008/09/07/rock-paper-shotgun-discovers-that-wow-is-a-dirty-word/ |archivedate=2012-07-28 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

== 主要人物 ==

本來Kieron Gillen是網站一份子，但於2010年9月30日，Kieron Gillen宣布，他不再參與Rock, Paper, Shotgun的內容，而更專注工作與漫畫，但也將繼續擔任網站董事，偶爾為網站寫作品。但於2010年接手Gillen的作家Quintin Smith也於2011年7月辭職。<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2011/07/04/announcing-quindependence-day/|title = Announcing: Quindependence Day|author = Quintin Smith|date = 2011-07-04|work = Rock, Paper, Shotgun|accessdate = 2011-08-28|quote = (...) I’m announcing that today, the fourth of July, or Quindependance day, will be my last day on the site.|archive-date = 2011-08-28|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110828060146/http://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2011/07/04/announcing-quindependence-day/|dead-url = no}}</ref>

